Wiper leader Kalonzo Musyoka will host the country&rsquo;s senior political leaders and dignitaries in Nairobi next week. The event will mark his crowning as Africa&rsquo;s top diplomat in 2016. Kalonzo was in August feted as the African Dignitary Man of the Year by &ldquo;We Care for Humanity&rdquo; New York, a global humanitarian organisation.The former VP was feted for his humanitarian works and conflict resolution efforts, including peace talks in Sudan. The founder of the organisation that feted him will be jetting in the country for the event t be held in a Nairobi hotel on October 18.The Black Tie dinner is an invite-only event. Organisers say they plan to celebrate the humanitarian work which the Kalonzo Musyoka Foundation has done. Kalonzo&rsquo;s Cord co-principals Raila Odinga (Cord) and Moses Wetang&rsquo;ula (Ford Kenya) will attend the event.